==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Atrophy
<hw>At"ro*phy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>atrophia</ets>, Gr. <?/; <grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ to nourish: cf.
F. <ets>atrophie</ets>.]</ety> <def>A wasting away from lack of
nourishment; diminution in bulk or slow emaciation of the body or of any
part.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atrophy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Atrophy
<hw>At"ro*phy</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Atrophied</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To cause to
waste away or become abortive; to starve or weaken.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atrophy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Atrophy
<hw>At"ro*phy</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To waste away; to
dwindle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atropia</ent>⟦br⟧
